%N A396995 Square array A(n,k), n >= 1, k >= 0, read by antidiagonals downwards, where column k is the expansion of B^k(x), where B(x) is the g.f. of A378576.
%H A396995 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A396995/b396995.txt">Antidiagonals n = 1..140, flattened</a>
%F A396995 G.f. B(x) satisfies B(x) = x*(1 + B^l(x)), where B^l(x) denotes the l-th iterate of B.
%F A396995 Let a(n,k,l) = [x^n] B^k(x), where B^k(x) is the k-th iterate of B.
%F A396995 a(n,0,l) = 0^(n-1) and a(n,k,l) = a(n,k-1,l) + Sum_{j=1..n-1} a(j,k+l-1,l) * a(n-j,k-1,l) for k > 0.
%F A396995 A(n,k) = a(n,k,6).
%e A396995 Square array begins:
%e A396995   1,     1,     1,     1,      1,      1,      1, ...
%e A396995   0,     1,     2,     3,      4,      5,      6, ...
%e A396995   0,     6,    14,    24,     36,     50,     66, ...
